<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98449148924259></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98449148924259><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98449148924259>RE: Songs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98449148924259#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=23765><span id=Scholar>Qmeryen</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 13th 8:51 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have my songs set on hot keys, makes it real easy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Just be sure to hit the button for the song you want to sing twice - the first is to cancel the song you are singing and the second is to actually sing the song.  I have my brusco's bellow on 8, Anthem D'Arms on 9 and healing on 10  (or 0) I just go back and forth.  Its easy and really works well<br>Onenote, lvl 12 bard on Xegony<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Qmeryen 35th lvl Druid Onenote 38th lvl Bard Qmeri&nbsp;&nbsp; 51st lvl Cleric</td></tr>
